  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "hackernews",
      "subsource": "news.ycombinator.com",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Real-time LLM Inference on Standard GPUs: 3k tokens/s per request",
      "url": "https://blog.kog.ai/real-time-llm-inference-on-standard-gpus-3-000-tokens-s-per-request/",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48321076",
      "score": 204,
      "comments": 91,
      "author": "NicoConstant",
      "published": "2026-05-29T09:47:23Z",
      "bullets": [
        "New optimization techniques achieve 3,000 tokens/sec per stream on standard GPUs like NVIDIA A100, bypassing traditional memory bandwidth bottlenecks.",
        "Achieving these speeds typically requires speculative decoding, highly optimized FP8/FP16 kernels, and aggressive KV cache management algorithms.",
        "Ultra-fast single-request throughput enables real-time agentic workflows, instantaneous multi-step reasoning, and interactive UX previously blocked by high latency."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "bijou64: A variable-length integer encoding",
      "url": "https://www.inkandswitch.com/tangents/bijou64/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/40broz",
      "score": 49,
      "comments": 6,
      "author": "justinweiss",
      "published": "2026-05-29T15:02:24Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Bijou64 encodes 64-bit integers using prefix-coded lengths instead of LEB128-style continuation bits, optimizing parsing performance.",
        "The format enables branchless decoding via CPU intrinsics like CLZ (Count Leading Zeros), reducing instruction count and pipeline stalls.",
        "It scales from 1 to 9 bytes, offering a highly efficient alternative for serialization formats and database index keys."
      ]
    },
